headline: Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Robert Half, Rumble, QuinStreet, and Ziff Davis Stocks Trade Down, What You Need To Know
summary: A number of stocks fell in the afternoon session after worries over worsening trade relations with China were triggered by critical comments from President Donald Trump. Trump targeted China's tightening controls on rare earth metals, which are vital components in many technology products from electric vehicles to defense systems. The president's tone and the suggestion of canceling a meeting with President Xi caused a rapid sell-off in the market.

headline: Could HPE's (HPE) AI-Powered Networking Push Reveal Its Next Growth Engine?
summary: In early October 2025, Nokia announced it had licensed technology assets from Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HPE) to enhance its AI-powered radio access network (RAN) automation, integrating HPE's RAN Intelligent Controller with Nokia's MantaRay platform and expanding Nokia's solutions in AI-driven network automation.
